HEADWORD: sentential
<hw>sen*ten"tial</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Comprising sentences; <as>as, a <ex>sentential</ex>
translation</as>.</def> <rj><au>Abp. Newcome.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Of or pertaining to a sentence, or full period;
<as>as, a <ex>sentential</ex> pause</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sententially</ent>⟦br⟧
